==== Blossom Altar ====
{{Blurimage|file=L-100 Blossom Altar.png|caption=The altar.}}
An alone, lotus-shaped brethren of the radio towers sits still in a forest yet unconquered by cranes. It seems to shiver, pulsate—lightly vibrate, as though the metallic shell is hiding the skin of something alive experiencing the cold, as though the inner, thin layer of unbreakable steel that wraps around it is an inescapable cage, barring whatever is inside from seeing what exists beyond and barring the beyond from what exists inside. It commonly reciprocates the sound of the radio field, playing it back through its center, unleashing the ethereal melody in a distorted form back into nature. It emits a cold aura around its structure, contrasted by the warmth of its shell. Below its foundation lies an intricate system of metallic roots that run through the terrain like butter; they jitter and lightly move in the stone, carving in small pockets of air with time, yet the shell never seems to be damaged or rusted.

The most notable aspect of the altar is its image distortion. Photographs up close are interfered with, and so are camcorders and audio devices. Video becomes unrecognizably crunched, audio becomes blown out and bassy, all while photographs take the smallest toll with simple, glossy image compression, as if purposefully letting its existence be spread through more than just word of mouth. 

