<br>
{{Template:Blurimage|file=L-100 Khofner.jpg|caption=A pet Khofner.}}
Round, cyclopic, shy furballs blend into the darkness, towering over society in their wake. As the only naturally occurring entity in the level, a majority of the populace keeps a Khofner as a pet; many wanderers describe their calming and relaxing effect as being akin to “cats,” an animal not too dissimilar to our [[Kats]]. Khofners are quite active in human custody, with their shyness quickly fading, becoming more integrated with people as though they were a family member. Aside from their calming effect, Khofners have been been noted to experience a strange comfort and interest in cranes, wire angels, radios (specifically, the noise emitted by the radio field), and the various other pieces of architecture scattered throughout the level, backed by an irrational, unsubduable fear and disdain of human-made constructs, and, despite domestication being possible, those who live in slums around the coast are unable to convince a Khofner to domesticate.

Their unblinking, glowing eyes are poignant even in the dark. Their human-like eyes, fluid and flexible, weave a deep feeling of disturbance and dread as a myriad of eyes stare at one from all angles. Their pack-like tendencies are volatile; it's common for swaths of Khofners to form for mere hours, just to disband soon after. Most packs are formed in-the-moment, usually to take advantage of utility poles for feeding as they nuzzle up to the metal and wires to consume the electricity for sustenance.

''Extras: '' [[Khofner Taming Guide|79:kra/khofner_taming_guide]]

=== Seawalkers ===
