{{Template:Blurimage|file=L-100 Caller.png|caption=The last one.}}
A tulpae of fear culminated in the Nymphaeaist Ravage, an attempted religious cleansing by the now-long-gone Astasia, the oldest known culture and people to have formed on the level. Callers were notably biblical in design, motifs that are in part thanks to the now-extinct [[Phenomenon 9|Wake Catholic Church]]’s own attempt at the total eradication of the "barbaric," resulting in the manifestation of a violent and aggressive mimicry of God. 

They assisted the Ravage through speech and fear. It possessed properties to fragment emotional responses and the ability to “call” on Nymphaeaists locations through the radio frequencies used by Astasians for public channel radio. Their appearance is described as headache-inducing, with the light flaps of their all-seeing wings being hypnotizing, a hypnosis that forms kaleidoscopic migraine auras of rapidly shifting, abstract shapes and colors.

Long after the ravage had been concluded, long after the Red Lotus wiped Astasians off the map, Callers kept existing, wandering aimlessly across the level. Their existence, a painful reminder to the Nymphaeaists who saw their loved ones aimlessly slaughtered and hunted like witches in the cleansing, and as the tragic memory faded, so did Callers; one by one, picked off and killed, until finally being brought to extinction by the Tehyovikwozhu militia in 1983. 
<br><br>
==Communities and Outposts==
For time's sake, the communities compiled here will only be those that have some sort of major significance or have made a major contribution to the populace or level, in no specific order.
<br><br>
<div class="log">
<div class="log-container"><div class="log-content"><br>
[[File:FTS-Anthra-flag.png|center|300px]]
<br><hr><br>
'''Anthra''' is a tightly organized, merchant-based group founded by ex-[[M.E.G.]] member Anthea Pawling (approx. 1893). Resting within the level's large swaths of now-uncontrolled territory, the group has a notable stranglehold on economic trade, with it being the primary choice for product distribution and selling for outsiders, resulting in its notably massive foreign currency reservoir only rivaled by [[Architect Industries]]. Small shops and stores controlled by Anthra are each denoted with a glowing, sixteen-pointed asterisk usually affixed on the side of the building, and many of the locations are in major travel hubs such as the central road or near borders. Although an exception exists, that being the Anthran Economy Zone, a plot of land the size of Kastenie run without government, a plot of land with the purpose of establishing a neutral, unified communal trading center for people and groups alike.

With its long history of sporadic, unstable leadership, its organization has become alien and anarchic from what it once used to be under Pawling, leading to the group fostering an almost pyramid scheme-like structure, further complicated and obfuscated with its winding branches and fractal-like composition, with each pyramid containing multiple others within.
</div></div>
</div>
<br>
<div class="log">
<div class="log-container"><div class="log-content"><br>
[[File:FTS-Kastenie-flag.png|center|300px]]
<br><hr><br>
'''Kastenie'''—or the State of Kastenie—is a small, neutral, self-described "scientocratic state" responsible for much of Level 79's scientific discovery, prowess, and advancement. The state largely prides itself on its people and beliefs deeply embedded in Geniocracy and Social Darwinism, with its small populace solely composed of scientists and researchers, a populace heavily monitored and afflicted by the dictatorial, constantly revolving "High Senate." Those born within the state are subject to a grueling and daunting 6-year-long education after their basic preliminary, from age 12 to 18, with those who fail being deported to groups like the Proletarium or CHF as either citizens or lesser—more commonly the latter.

Many describe the scientocracy as a self-fulfilling prophecy—those in the High Senate are those smart enough to realise the corruption and horrid nature of the system; people that are then manipulated into rule with material promises to further continue the unbreakable loop.
</div></div>
</div>
<br>
<div class="log">
<div class="log-container"><div class="log-content"><br>
[[File:FTS-CHF-flag.png|center|300px]]
<br><hr><br>
Outside of Nymphaeism's wide reach on the level, the '''Confederation of the Holy Flower''' (CHF) stands tall as a conglomerate—and representative—of 5 separate nations, culturally unified under the level-born "Florist" religion. While inherently separate and widely different in nature, Florism draws influences from Nymphaeaism; not only in its flower-based symbolism but also in structure with its Florist Church. Florism believes that the Wake is a result of God's death, with the fragments of his self being dispersed, pollinating the flowers that would eventually bloom into what we know as irreality, with the flower-based symbolism of the religion extending to more than just symbolic preference but also the Wake's structure as a whole. It believes that God is a title that can be redeemed by anyone and that the Wake is the direct access point towards the redemption of this title.

As a nation, the CHF is highly capitalist and classifies as an autocratic democracy, flawed to its very core, with a leadership similar to Ruphis, although lesser in severity. Comparatively to other nations within the level, the CHF is the most basic and least outlandish in ideology, with its influence primarily standing in trade, military strength, and as the direct source of most tulpae-ified folklore to roam the level.
</div></div>
</div>
<br>
<div class="log">
<div class="log-container"><div class="log-content"><br>
[[File:FTS-Mechta-flag.png|center|300px]]
<br><hr><br>
Founded by ex-Nexusian military general Zvezda Shiprovski in the wake of [[Auto Nexus]]' infamous Silent Coup (approx. 1952), the '''Nexusian Republic of Mechta''' is a breakaway state moulded by Zvezda's own ideological beliefs: beliefs of self-sustainability, secularity, cultural liberalism, total military control, and prosperity. The state's meddling in geopolitics is minimal, as much of its time is spent focusing and tackling local issues, cleanly reflected by almost all states within Level 79—regardless of ideology—sharing a reciprocated, neutral stance with the republic. Elections are traditionally absent, with group leadership being reserved to the Shiprovski dynasty, although crisis'—such as an inability for the current leader to govern (regardless of the reason)—are exempt, with elections for temporary leadership being held immediately.
</div></div>
</div>
<br>
<div class="log">
<div class="log-container"><div class="log-content"><br>
[[File:FTS-Tehyovikwozhu-flag.png|center|300px]]
<br><hr><br>
The '''Ncipetherazi Republic of Tehyovikwozhu''' is a so-called "cultural colony"—the biggest of its kind; an independent entity technically classified as part of Ncipetheraz due to its deep-rooted cultural connection. Formed as a result of the Ncipetherazi Level 79 Repopulation Program (approx. 1886), the colony reserves full independence, although some of its actions are under the lenient jurisdiction of the Ncipetherazi council. The national structure is also no different from its home country, with a strict, traditional Sylvainist leadership and economy, as well as a focus on Nymphaeaist ideals and beliefs.
</div></div>
</div>
<br>
<div class="log">
<div class="log-container"><div class="log-content"><br>
[[File:FTS-Rahaullinen-flag.png|center|300px]]
<br><hr><br>
The '''[[Anima|Socialist Republic of Rauhallinen]]''' (approx. 1981) is a state founded as a response—and direct antithesis—to the Proletarium takeover of the Ruphis Principalities by the minority Nymphaeaist populace. Founded by Finnish-born Ruphan Antton Järveläinen, Rauhallinen is a democratic, open government state majorly influenced by Ncipetherazi politics and some [[Republic of Aurielle|Auriellen]] thought. It keeps close ties with Ncipetheraz and, by proxy, the neighboring Tehyovikwozhu and has been involved multiple times in various regional conflicts, such as 2008's [[Anima/Ruphis-Ncipetheraz Border Skirmishes|Ruphis-Ncipetherazi Border Skirmishes]]. Aurielle's political influence on the nation can be seen with its lack of reservation in geopolitics, and its common, almost "heroic" attitude towards minor conflicts in the level has given it the inflammatory title of "colonial lapdog" or "colonial qutzgoat".

Rauhallineni influence is primarily found within its external police force, largely based on the [[Backrooms Investigation Foundation|B.I.F.]], a somewhat effective, rigid secret service responsible for mass-scale crackdowns and assassinations of criminals seen as generally problematic by the wider populace, such as the Sightseer and [[Atrego|Atregoan]] sympathizers.
</div></div>
</div>
<br>
<div class="log">
<div class="log-container"><div class="log-content"><br>
