<br><hr><br>
The '''Ruphis Proletarium''' is the most infamous major group in the level, and perhaps even outside of it, only rivaled by the likes of Z.E.T.A. and [[Atrego]]; its formation as we know it in 1966 was established after the Black April Coup within the then-failing United Principalities of Rupha, resulting in the establishment of an autocratic, socialist state with a deep, close alignment to Kastenie and the CHF.

Despite being coastal, the Proletarium is impressively industrialized—masterfully using the level's ambiguous inner workings to their fullest extent, with key parts of Ruphis being mining, industry, and self-sufficiency. Interestingly, the so-called "Proletarium Socialist" doctrine takes heavy inspiration from the Ncipetherazi Zedkwoyo dictatorship. It's cultural manipulation with the intent of normalizing violations of human rights; the good—albeit still slave-like—conditions of the working class (or, as they're called, "proles"); and the castle city-like infrastructure of its capital, Fort Mulhausen.
